Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the @diced sweet potato{200%grams} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{18-20%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a medium #bowl{}, roughly mash two thirds of the black beans with the back of a
#fork{}, leaving the other third whole.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
@diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until its starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir in the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}, cook for
~{1%min}.

Add the whole and mashed black beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams},
@water for the beans{75%milliliters}, half of the @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add
less if you prefer things milder) to the pan. Season with salt and pepper.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and cook until thickened, ~{5-6%mins},
stirring occasionally.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce becomes too thick.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a large baking tray in a single
layer and rub each with a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and bake on the
middle shelf of the oven until golden and crispy, ~{4-6%mins}.

> TIP: Tostada means 'toasted', so make sure they're crispy!

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges.

In a medium bowl, add the tomato chunks, lime juice from a lime wedge,
@sugar for the dressing{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and
season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

In a small bowl, mix together the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and remaining chipotle paste.

Just before you're ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{20%grams} in with the
tomato chunks.

Transfer your tostadas to your serving plates, spoon over the chorizo, black beans
and roasted sweet potato.

Top with the tomato and rocket salad, crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{100%grams}
and drizzle over the chipotle mayo.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside.

> TIP: Tostadas are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!